    "updated_at": "2016-08-22T23:05:56Z",
    "body": "When using 'Window Spy' i measure that all my displays have a size of native*1.5.\n\nWhen giving X/Y cords to position a Electron BrowserWindow it works like this:\n\n### **monitor = 3840x2160@1.5scaling**\n\n**Situation as if my monitor is 2560x1440** \npositions it all the way in the upper right corner. (like this: http://imgur.com/ZkBrmVg)\n\n```\nBrowserWindow({\n    width:560, height:730,\n    x: 2000, y: 0,\n    frame: false\n});\n```\n\n**situation as if my monitor is 3840x2160**\n(like this: http://imgur.com/7gQZoKT)  everything in between x:2000 and x:2282 will position it in between 2 monitors. 560/2=280 so that makes sense\n\n```\nBrowserWindow({\n    width:560, height:730,\n    x: 2282, y: 0,\n    frame: false\n});\n```\n\npositioning it on the 1080p monitor that has no scaling works fine (http://imgur.com/Nc5YvUX)\n\n```\nBrowserWindow({\n    width:560, height:730,\n    x: 3840+1920-560, y: 0,\n    frame: false\n});\n\n```\n"
